<p>I am trying to do commit and push using <code>Mercurial.Net</code> library:</p>  <pre><code>var repo = new Repository(repositoryPath);  var branchCommand = new BranchCommand { Name = branch }; repo.Branch(branchCommand);  var commitCommand = new CommitCommand { Message = commitMessage, OverrideAuthor = author }; repo.Commit(commitCommand);  var pushCommand = new PushCommand { AllowCreatingNewBranch = true, Force = true, }; repo.Push(pushCommand); </code></pre>  <p>On <code>repo.Push(pushCommand)</code> it throws an exception <code>Mercurial.MercurialExecutionException</code> with message 'abort: Access is denied'.</p>  <p>The question is: Is there any way in <code>Mercurial.Net</code> to get the output of mercurial console?</p>